Cape Town hosted Africa’s finest ultra-distance athletes this weekend, the Two Oceans Marathon. There was fierce rivalry among some of the continent’s top distance-running countries, and no fewer than representatives from 27 African countries. While the likes of Namibia and Botswana boasted significant numbers, five nations battled for supremacy up front - South Africa, Zimbabwe, Kenya, Ethiopia and Lesotho. Khayelitsha marathoner Lungile Gongqa claimed victory in a time of 3 hours 9 minutes 43 seconds. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
